  "description": "<p>分类: <a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/category/misc-gadgets/\" rel=\"tag\">精彩杂录</a></p><div style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2013/07/03/gregory-lee-becomes-president-of-samsungs-us-mobile-division/\"><img src=\"http://www.blogcdn.com/cn.engadget.com/media/2013/07/samsung-gregory-lee.jpg\" style=\"margin: 4px;\" /></a></div>\n\n<div><br />\n在今天三星美国迎来了一场人士变动，原全球营销运营主管李宗锡（Gregory Lee）将接替 Dale Sohn 成为新一任的移动部门总裁，后者则会前往韩国担任移动 CEO 申宗均（JK Shin）身边的行政顾问一职。三星方面目前还未公布这场变动背后的原因，但我们感觉这对 Sohn 来说应该算是一次升职。毕竟三星最近在智能手机领域的成功很大程度上是依靠其在美国市场的表现，考虑到这一点的话，Sohn 的建议对申老大来说应该会份量很重啊。<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n经由：<a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/2013/07/03/gregory-lee-becomes-president-of-samsungs-us-mobile-division/\">Engadget</a><br />\n引用来源：<a href=\"http://www.samsung.com/us/aboutsamsung/samsung_electronics/management/\" target=\"_blank\">Samsung</a><br />\n更多资讯：<a href=\"http://lifestyleasia.com/features/luxe-toys/a-moment-with-gregory-lee-of-president-and-ceo-of-samsung-asia-11323\" target=\"_blank\">Lifestyle Asia</a></div><p><h6 style=\"clear: both; padding: 8px 0 0 0; height: 2px; font-size: 1px; border: 0; margin: 0; padding: 0;\"></h6><a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2013/07/03/gregory-lee-becomes-president-of-samsungs-us-mobile-division/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent link to this entry\">此文章网址</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/forward/20648626/\" title=\"Send this entry to a friend via email\">转寄此文章</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2013/07/03/gregory-lee-becomes-president-of-samsungs-us-mobile-division/#comments\" title=\"View reader comments on this entry\">回应</a><hr size=\"1\" />", 
